WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.410 align:middle line:90%
[WHOOSH]

00:00:02.410 --> 00:00:04.820 align:middle line:90%


00:00:04.820 --> 00:00:10.368 align:middle line:90%
[THEME MUSIC]

00:00:10.368 --> 00:00:12.410 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE NOORY: What is
it about matchmaking that

00:00:12.410 --> 00:00:13.358 align:middle line:90%
is satisfying for you?

00:00:13.358 --> 00:00:15.650 align:middle line:84%
>>MARLA MARTENSON: I get to
meet so many amazing people

00:00:15.650 --> 00:00:19.040 align:middle line:84%
from all different backgrounds,
and everybody wants love.

00:00:19.040 --> 00:00:21.488 align:middle line:84%
Matchmaking can get a
little shallow sometimes

00:00:21.488 --> 00:00:23.030 align:middle line:84%
in what people are
looking for, and I

00:00:23.030 --> 00:00:25.530 align:middle line:84%
like that spiritual
aspect to balance it out.

00:00:25.530 --> 00:00:28.220 align:middle line:84%
I get some intuition, and
I'll even send energy healing

00:00:28.220 --> 00:00:29.120 align:middle line:90%
to my clients.

00:00:29.120 --> 00:00:30.980 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Didn't you
match up a woman

00:00:30.980 --> 00:00:34.370 align:middle line:84%
with a prominent owner of
a professional sports team

00:00:34.370 --> 00:00:35.795 align:middle line:84%
and they ended up
getting married?

00:00:35.795 --> 00:00:41.590 align:middle line:90%


00:00:41.590 --> 00:00:42.970 align:middle line:84%
Well, welcome to
"Beyond Belief."

00:00:42.970 --> 00:00:44.680 align:middle line:84%
We've got a fascinating
guest for you.

00:00:44.680 --> 00:00:47.740 align:middle line:10%
Marla Martenson based
out of Los Angeles

00:00:47.740 --> 00:00:50.410 align:middle line:10%
is a professional matchmaker.

00:00:50.410 --> 00:00:53.200 align:middle line:84%
Marla is also a life
coach, energy healer,

00:00:53.200 --> 00:00:54.140 align:middle line:90%
and intuitive reader.

00:00:54.140 --> 00:00:55.390 align:middle line:90%
Welcome to the program, Marla.

00:00:55.390 --> 00:00:56.390 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTENSON: Hi, George.

00:00:56.390 --> 00:00:57.290 align:middle line:90%
Thanks for having me.

00:00:57.290 --> 00:00:59.170 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: How did you get
involved in matchmaking?

00:00:59.170 --> 00:01:00.170 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTENSON: Oh my gosh.

00:01:00.170 --> 00:01:00.970 align:middle line:90%
It was a fluke.

00:01:00.970 --> 00:01:03.303 align:middle line:10%
It's so interesting, because
people always want to know,

00:01:03.303 --> 00:01:05.200 align:middle line:10%
is this something you
always wanted to do?

00:01:05.200 --> 00:01:08.030 align:middle line:10%
But I was an actress/waitress
for the first 20 years

00:01:08.030 --> 00:01:08.830 align:middle line:10%
of my life.

00:01:08.830 --> 00:01:09.220 align:middle line:10%
>>NOORY: Really?

00:01:09.220 --> 00:01:09.520 align:middle line:10%
>>MARTENSON: Yeah.

00:01:09.520 --> 00:01:11.920 align:middle line:10%
I was doing TV commercials,
modeling, little gigs

00:01:11.920 --> 00:01:12.890 align:middle line:10%
and things.

00:01:12.890 --> 00:01:17.890 align:middle line:10%
And then when I was 39, I had
a pivotal point in my life

00:01:17.890 --> 00:01:20.620 align:middle line:10%
where my father passed
away from cancer.

00:01:20.620 --> 00:01:22.480 align:middle line:84%
I usually ended up
waiting on tables

00:01:22.480 --> 00:01:23.900 align:middle line:90%
more than I was acting, right?

00:01:23.900 --> 00:01:25.690 align:middle line:84%
And so I was like, I
need something else.

00:01:25.690 --> 00:01:27.910 align:middle line:84%
Please, you know, I
was praying to God.

00:01:27.910 --> 00:01:30.770 align:middle line:84%
I'd go in churches and leave
little notes, you know?

00:01:30.770 --> 00:01:33.880 align:middle line:84%
And I was doing all this
affirmations and stuff.

00:01:33.880 --> 00:01:36.760 align:middle line:84%
I don't know what I'm going to
do, what skills that I have,

00:01:36.760 --> 00:01:38.660 align:middle line:84%
but I want to do
something different.

00:01:38.660 --> 00:01:41.770 align:middle line:84%
And that's when I first
met Adolfo, my husband.

00:01:41.770 --> 00:01:46.030 align:middle line:84%
And he had a friend who was
taking over the management

00:01:46.030 --> 00:01:48.950 align:middle line:84%
position at a video
dating service and said,

00:01:48.950 --> 00:01:51.460 align:middle line:84%
hey, if you want a part-time
gig, we need somebody.

00:01:51.460 --> 00:01:53.710 align:middle line:84%
So I started working
at this place.

00:01:53.710 --> 00:01:54.970 align:middle line:90%
I was the videographer.

00:01:54.970 --> 00:01:58.570 align:middle line:84%
It was doing videos and
working the front desk.

00:01:58.570 --> 00:02:01.510 align:middle line:84%
And then from there, I went over
to a Beverly Hills matchmaking

00:02:01.510 --> 00:02:03.653 align:middle line:84%
service, which was the
high-end, the more--

00:02:03.653 --> 00:02:04.570 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Very upscale.

00:02:04.570 --> 00:02:05.560 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTENSON: Upscale.

00:02:05.560 --> 00:02:08.050 align:middle line:84%
And I ended up working
there for seven years.

00:02:08.050 --> 00:02:11.500 align:middle line:84%
Started writing books, because
I had to still be creative

00:02:11.500 --> 00:02:13.250 align:middle line:90%
since I'd dropped the acting.

00:02:13.250 --> 00:02:16.060 align:middle line:84%
Then in 2010, I
went out on my own

00:02:16.060 --> 00:02:17.710 align:middle line:84%
and started my own
matchmaking service

00:02:17.710 --> 00:02:18.820 align:middle line:90%
with a business partner.

00:02:18.820 --> 00:02:19.737 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Good for you.

00:02:19.737 --> 00:02:21.430 align:middle line:90%
What is a soul mate?

00:02:21.430 --> 00:02:23.980 align:middle line:84%
We hear so many
different definitions.

00:02:23.980 --> 00:02:25.750 align:middle line:84%
What do you think
a soul mate is?

00:02:25.750 --> 00:02:29.030 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTENSON: Well, I think
that we travel in soul groups.

00:02:29.030 --> 00:02:32.772 align:middle line:84%
So you and Adolfo, you
know, you guys are friends.

00:02:32.772 --> 00:02:33.730 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: He's my buddy.

00:02:33.730 --> 00:02:35.188 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTENSON: Yeah,
he's your buddy.

00:02:35.188 --> 00:02:37.600 align:middle line:84%
You guys maybe have had
past lives together.

00:02:37.600 --> 00:02:39.010 align:middle line:90%
My dog Macy's a soul mate.

00:02:39.010 --> 00:02:40.540 align:middle line:90%
So we go in soul groups.

00:02:40.540 --> 00:02:42.100 align:middle line:84%
And sometimes one
of these people

00:02:42.100 --> 00:02:44.587 align:middle line:84%
could be a romantic interest,
and they can come in,

00:02:44.587 --> 00:02:45.670 align:middle line:90%
and that's your soul mate.

00:02:45.670 --> 00:02:48.130 align:middle line:90%
And I think really, it's more--

00:02:48.130 --> 00:02:49.720 align:middle line:84%
in the romantic
sense, it's somebody

00:02:49.720 --> 00:02:51.460 align:middle line:84%
that you have a
great affinity with

00:02:51.460 --> 00:02:54.100 align:middle line:84%
and that you're going to
have great lessons to learn

00:02:54.100 --> 00:02:56.310 align:middle line:90%
together and be together.

00:02:56.310 --> 00:02:58.600 align:middle line:84%
It's like we're soul
to soul, you know?

00:02:58.600 --> 00:03:01.690 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: I hear so many
people complain afterwards

00:03:01.690 --> 00:03:04.810 align:middle line:84%
that if they have a breakup
in their relationship,

00:03:04.810 --> 00:03:08.475 align:middle line:84%
they're distraught because
they think, oh my god.

00:03:08.475 --> 00:03:10.270 align:middle line:90%
I've lost my soul mate.

00:03:10.270 --> 00:03:12.670 align:middle line:84%
Was that person intended
to be a soul mate?

00:03:12.670 --> 00:03:14.170 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTENSON: Yeah,
well, a soul mate

00:03:14.170 --> 00:03:16.337 align:middle line:84%
doesn't mean that you're
always going-- you're going

00:03:16.337 --> 00:03:17.440 align:middle line:90%
to stay together for life.

00:03:17.440 --> 00:03:19.870 align:middle line:84%
They could come in for a
certain purpose, to teach--

00:03:19.870 --> 00:03:20.690 align:middle line:90%
it's always--

00:03:20.690 --> 00:03:21.820 align:middle line:84%
it's always going to
teach you something.

00:03:21.820 --> 00:03:23.320 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And it doesn't
mean just one person.

00:03:23.320 --> 00:03:24.580 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTENSON: Doesn't
mean just one person,

00:03:24.580 --> 00:03:25.960 align:middle line:84%
and it's not always
going to be easy.

00:03:25.960 --> 00:03:27.490 align:middle line:84%
You think, oh, my
soul mate, we're

00:03:27.490 --> 00:03:28.540 align:middle line:90%
going to do everything the same.

00:03:28.540 --> 00:03:29.500 align:middle line:90%
We're going to think the same.

00:03:29.500 --> 00:03:31.465 align:middle line:84%
We're going to cut our
carrots the same way.

00:03:31.465 --> 00:03:34.270 align:middle line:84%
[LAUGHS] They're going
to show you some things

00:03:34.270 --> 00:03:37.180 align:middle line:84%
that you need to learn some
lessons, life lessons, soul

00:03:37.180 --> 00:03:38.020 align:middle line:90%
lessons.

00:03:38.020 --> 00:03:39.655 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: When you
match people, what

00:03:39.655 --> 00:03:40.780 align:middle line:90%
are you trying to look for?

00:03:40.780 --> 00:03:44.230 align:middle line:84%
I mean, do you actually look
at the personalities of the two

00:03:44.230 --> 00:03:45.520 align:middle line:90%
individuals?

00:03:45.520 --> 00:03:48.515 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTENSON: Well, since the men
are my paying clients and men

00:03:48.515 --> 00:03:49.315 align:middle line:90%
are so visual--

00:03:49.315 --> 00:03:51.850 align:middle line:84%
[LAUGHS] so first,
I've got to look

00:03:51.850 --> 00:03:54.765 align:middle line:84%
at the looks type they like,
the location, the age range.

00:03:54.765 --> 00:03:57.140 align:middle line:84%
Maybe there's a religious
background they're looking for.

00:03:57.140 --> 00:03:57.880 align:middle line:90%
Do they want kids?

00:03:57.880 --> 00:03:58.690 align:middle line:90%
Do they have kids?

00:03:58.690 --> 00:04:01.810 align:middle line:84%
And now, George, with this
political climate we have--

00:04:01.810 --> 00:04:04.930 align:middle line:84%
never in my life did I have
to ask political affiliation

00:04:04.930 --> 00:04:05.915 align:middle line:90%
or preference, and--

00:04:05.915 --> 00:04:07.040 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: That comes up now?

00:04:07.040 --> 00:04:07.600 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTENSON: Yes.

00:04:07.600 --> 00:04:09.740 align:middle line:84%
There'll be-- somebody
maybe is a liberal and says,

00:04:09.740 --> 00:04:11.157 align:middle line:84%
I would never date
a conservative.

00:04:11.157 --> 00:04:13.060 align:middle line:84%
A conservative says, I
won't date a liberal.

00:04:13.060 --> 00:04:15.860 align:middle line:84%
And it gets pretty-- it
could be heated on a date.

00:04:15.860 --> 00:04:17.709 align:middle line:84%
So I have to screen
for that now.

00:04:17.709 --> 00:04:19.039 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: That's intriguing.

00:04:19.039 --> 00:04:19.839 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTENSON: Yeah.

00:04:19.839 --> 00:04:21.640 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Do you do
any of it by computer?

00:04:21.640 --> 00:04:23.650 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTENSON: Well, I
hand-match everybody,

00:04:23.650 --> 00:04:27.430 align:middle line:84%
but I send them their
matches by text or on email.

00:04:27.430 --> 00:04:29.230 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What's
your success rate?

00:04:29.230 --> 00:04:29.740 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTENSON: All right.

00:04:29.740 --> 00:04:30.670 align:middle line:90%
Interesting question.

00:04:30.670 --> 00:04:34.040 align:middle line:84%
So success rate
could really mean

00:04:34.040 --> 00:04:36.040 align:middle line:84%
I'm successful in
setting the client up

00:04:36.040 --> 00:04:38.440 align:middle line:84%
with the type of person
they're looking for.

00:04:38.440 --> 00:04:40.900 align:middle line:84%
But I think people mean success
rate, how many people get

00:04:40.900 --> 00:04:42.250 align:middle line:90%
married, stay in a relationship?

00:04:42.250 --> 00:04:43.330 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: That's right.

00:04:43.330 --> 00:04:44.727 align:middle line:90%
Second date, third date?

00:04:44.727 --> 00:04:46.060 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTENSON: I've had a lot of--

00:04:46.060 --> 00:04:47.710 align:middle line:84%
over the years,
two decades-- a lot

00:04:47.710 --> 00:04:50.440 align:middle line:84%
of marriages, a lot of
people in relationships.

00:04:50.440 --> 00:04:52.180 align:middle line:90%
And then sometimes they won't.

00:04:52.180 --> 00:04:54.713 align:middle line:84%
If they're too picky,
they've got a list too long,

00:04:54.713 --> 00:04:57.130 align:middle line:84%
maybe they're not really going
to get into a relationship.

00:04:57.130 --> 00:04:59.200 align:middle line:84%
I've had some over
the years, couples

00:04:59.200 --> 00:05:00.940 align:middle line:84%
get married, got
divorced, and then

00:05:00.940 --> 00:05:02.368 align:middle line:90%
they came and signed up again.

00:05:02.368 --> 00:05:03.910 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Is it
tempting for you, when

00:05:03.910 --> 00:05:08.560 align:middle line:84%
you meet people who are friends
of, let's say, your husband,

00:05:08.560 --> 00:05:10.250 align:middle line:90%
trying to match them up?

00:05:10.250 --> 00:05:13.330 align:middle line:84%
Do you go beyond
the call of duty?

00:05:13.330 --> 00:05:16.330 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTENSON: Well, I haven't
had any of my husband's friends

00:05:16.330 --> 00:05:19.870 align:middle line:84%
as clients, but I have tried
to help a couple of them.

00:05:19.870 --> 00:05:22.270 align:middle line:84%
And of course,
you know, you want

00:05:22.270 --> 00:05:24.680 align:middle line:90%
to see our friends be happy.

00:05:24.680 --> 00:05:25.480 align:middle line:90%
So I'll do that.

00:05:25.480 --> 00:05:26.500 align:middle line:90%
I play Cupid, you know?

00:05:26.500 --> 00:05:28.570 align:middle line:84%
It's hard not-- it's
hard to shut it off.

00:05:28.570 --> 00:05:29.830 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: You fling arrows?

00:05:29.830 --> 00:05:30.850 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTENSON: Yes.

00:05:30.850 --> 00:05:32.350 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And you
hit a few, once.

00:05:32.350 --> 00:05:33.445 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTENSON: I hit some.

00:05:33.445 --> 00:05:35.750 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Are people
appreciative of what you do?

00:05:35.750 --> 00:05:36.550 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTENSON: Yeah.

00:05:36.550 --> 00:05:38.950 align:middle line:84%
You know, I'm bringing a
healing to people in a way,

00:05:38.950 --> 00:05:41.810 align:middle line:84%
because even if they don't end
up in a long-term relationship,

00:05:41.810 --> 00:05:43.780 align:middle line:84%
it's that relationship
that we have.

00:05:43.780 --> 00:05:45.730 align:middle line:84%
Maybe they get some
coaching from me

00:05:45.730 --> 00:05:49.100 align:middle line:84%
or some healing or a different
perspective in some way.

00:05:49.100 --> 00:05:50.500 align:middle line:90%
And you know, they really are--

00:05:50.500 --> 00:05:51.820 align:middle line:90%
it's very rewarding for me.

00:05:51.820 --> 00:05:53.195 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What has
been really one

00:05:53.195 --> 00:05:55.240 align:middle line:84%
of the most satisfying
things you've done,

00:05:55.240 --> 00:05:57.680 align:middle line:84%
a story that you
can relate for us?

00:05:57.680 --> 00:05:58.720 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTENSON: Oh, yeah.

00:05:58.720 --> 00:06:00.700 align:middle line:90%
Well, there was this one couple.

00:06:00.700 --> 00:06:02.620 align:middle line:84%
This was a couple where
I knew immediately.

00:06:02.620 --> 00:06:05.230 align:middle line:84%
When the man joined, I
said, I-- and he told me--

00:06:05.230 --> 00:06:05.860 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: You had
the right person.

00:06:05.860 --> 00:06:06.130 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTENSON: Yes.

00:06:06.130 --> 00:06:07.840 align:middle line:84%
When he told me what he
was looking for, I said,

00:06:07.840 --> 00:06:09.040 align:middle line:90%
I have the right lady.

00:06:09.040 --> 00:06:12.820 align:middle line:84%
I introduced them and we ended
up going to their wedding.

00:06:12.820 --> 00:06:15.117 align:middle line:90%
Adolfo played music.

00:06:15.117 --> 00:06:17.200 align:middle line:84%
They had five different
musical-- they had a harp,

00:06:17.200 --> 00:06:18.890 align:middle line:90%
they had piano, they had--

00:06:18.890 --> 00:06:19.690 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Perfect.

00:06:19.690 --> 00:06:20.020 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTENSON: Yeah.

00:06:20.020 --> 00:06:21.880 align:middle line:84%
A gift for me there,
champagne toast.

00:06:21.880 --> 00:06:23.590 align:middle line:90%
It was just beautiful.

00:06:23.590 --> 00:06:24.910 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, it was really exciting.

00:06:24.910 --> 00:06:25.660 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: And it worked.

00:06:25.660 --> 00:06:26.240 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTENSON: It worked.

00:06:26.240 --> 00:06:26.530 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:06:26.530 --> 00:06:27.905 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Are they
still together?

00:06:27.905 --> 00:06:30.070 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTENSON: [LAUGHS]
That was back--

00:06:30.070 --> 00:06:32.380 align:middle line:84%
that was, like, 15 years
ago, and you know what?

00:06:32.380 --> 00:06:33.850 align:middle line:90%
They are not still together.

00:06:33.850 --> 00:06:35.630 align:middle line:90%
But it was a beautiful--

00:06:35.630 --> 00:06:37.420 align:middle line:84%
I mean, while it
lasted, it was great.

00:06:37.420 --> 00:06:37.750 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Right.

00:06:37.750 --> 00:06:38.560 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTENSON: Yeah.

00:06:38.560 --> 00:06:40.180 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Regina
Meredith runs a show

00:06:40.180 --> 00:06:41.830 align:middle line:90%
on Gaia called "Open Minds."

00:06:41.830 --> 00:06:45.450 align:middle line:84%
She talked with Arielle
Ford, whom I think you know,

00:06:45.450 --> 00:06:48.010 align:middle line:90%
about finding love.

00:06:48.010 --> 00:06:50.560 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA MEREDITH:
Ever since the addition

00:06:50.560 --> 00:06:54.400 align:middle line:84%
of new age culture
to society, it

00:06:54.400 --> 00:06:56.875 align:middle line:84%
seems to have almost
created a greater divide.

00:06:56.875 --> 00:06:58.250 align:middle line:90%
>>ARIELLE FORD: Yes.

00:06:58.250 --> 00:07:00.500 align:middle line:84%
>>MEREDITH: It hasn't done
what it was supposed to do,

00:07:00.500 --> 00:07:02.900 align:middle line:84%
which is to create
bridges to one another.

00:07:02.900 --> 00:07:05.525 align:middle line:84%
It's created a tremendous
amount of spiritual arrogance.

00:07:05.525 --> 00:07:06.400 align:middle line:90%
>>FORD: And judgment.

00:07:06.400 --> 00:07:07.442 align:middle line:90%
>>MEREDITH: And judgment.

00:07:07.442 --> 00:07:09.970 align:middle line:84%
>>FORD: And the truth
is, men experience

00:07:09.970 --> 00:07:13.610 align:middle line:84%
and express spirituality
differently than we do.

00:07:13.610 --> 00:07:16.150 align:middle line:84%
So we may want to sit
in the Mile High Church,

00:07:16.150 --> 00:07:18.760 align:middle line:84%
at the Unity Church,
and read certain books.

00:07:18.760 --> 00:07:21.610 align:middle line:10%
And if your guy is
coaching Little League

00:07:21.610 --> 00:07:25.900 align:middle line:10%
and volunteering at Big Brothers
and helping your mother get

00:07:25.900 --> 00:07:28.240 align:middle line:10%
in and out of the
car and just being

00:07:28.240 --> 00:07:31.420 align:middle line:10%
an all-around good
human being, what could

00:07:31.420 --> 00:07:33.495 align:middle line:10%
be more spiritual than that?

00:07:33.495 --> 00:07:34.528 align:middle line:90%
>>MEREDITH: Exactly.

00:07:34.528 --> 00:07:36.820 align:middle line:84%
>>FORD: You know, and yet,
when I talk to single women,

00:07:36.820 --> 00:07:39.610 align:middle line:84%
the first thing they say is, oh,
well, I want a spiritual guy.

00:07:39.610 --> 00:07:41.152 align:middle line:84%
>>MEREDITH: I've
heard this so often.

00:07:41.152 --> 00:07:44.065 align:middle line:84%
And most of those people
actually are alone.

00:07:44.065 --> 00:07:44.890 align:middle line:90%
>>FORD: Yes.

00:07:44.890 --> 00:07:47.755 align:middle line:10%
They're alone with their
"Conversations with God"

00:07:47.755 --> 00:07:50.500 align:middle line:10%
books and their workbooks
and their practices

00:07:50.500 --> 00:07:51.375 align:middle line:10%
and their chanting.

00:07:51.375 --> 00:07:52.750 align:middle line:10%
You know, I had
this conversation

00:07:52.750 --> 00:07:55.390 align:middle line:10%
with Elizabeth Gilbert who
wrote "Eat, Pray, Love."

00:07:55.390 --> 00:07:58.960 align:middle line:84%
And I said to her, what do you
love most about your husband?

00:07:58.960 --> 00:08:00.670 align:middle line:84%
And she said, well,
my history was

00:08:00.670 --> 00:08:04.630 align:middle line:84%
to be with guys who would go
to meditation retreats with me.

00:08:04.630 --> 00:08:07.900 align:middle line:84%
She said, but my husband
is never going to do yoga.

00:08:07.900 --> 00:08:09.490 align:middle line:90%
He's never going to meditate.

00:08:09.490 --> 00:08:12.370 align:middle line:84%
He's certainly never
doing a green juice fast.

00:08:12.370 --> 00:08:15.520 align:middle line:84%
But when I walk into
a room, his eyes

00:08:15.520 --> 00:08:17.950 align:middle line:84%
light up like it's
Christmas morning.

00:08:17.950 --> 00:08:21.340 align:middle line:10%
And he takes me by the hand
and leads me into the kitchen,

00:08:21.340 --> 00:08:24.730 align:middle line:10%
and he puts my feet up and
he hands me a glass of wine,

00:08:24.730 --> 00:08:26.560 align:middle line:10%
and then he cooks me dinner.

00:08:26.560 --> 00:08:28.060 align:middle line:90%
>>MEREDITH: Mm.

00:08:28.060 --> 00:08:30.010 align:middle line:90%
That's divine, right?

00:08:30.010 --> 00:08:31.060 align:middle line:90%
>>FORD: And she's happy.

00:08:31.060 --> 00:08:35.140 align:middle line:84%
And she understands that she
is a meditating, chanting,

00:08:35.140 --> 00:08:39.100 align:middle line:84%
green juice fasting kind
of girl, and he is not.

00:08:39.100 --> 00:08:40.270 align:middle line:90%
But he loves her.

00:08:40.270 --> 00:08:41.980 align:middle line:10%
He's devoted to her.

00:08:41.980 --> 00:08:43.659 align:middle line:10%
He's crazy about her.

00:08:43.659 --> 00:08:45.890 align:middle line:10%
And who wouldn't want that?

00:08:45.890 --> 00:08:49.750 align:middle line:10%
And yet, by most people's
standards, is he's spiritual?

00:08:49.750 --> 00:08:51.100 align:middle line:90%
Well, yes, in his own way.

00:08:51.100 --> 00:08:55.600 align:middle line:84%
Because he puts all that love in
the food, which he feeds to her

00:08:55.600 --> 00:08:56.932 align:middle line:90%
to nourish her body and soul.

00:08:56.932 --> 00:08:58.390 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What do
you think of that?

00:08:58.390 --> 00:08:59.320 align:middle line:90%
Is she spot on?

00:08:59.320 --> 00:09:01.860 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTENSON: Well, that
describes me and my husband.

00:09:01.860 --> 00:09:06.700 align:middle line:84%
I'm the green juice woo-woo
woman, and Adolfo's not.

00:09:06.700 --> 00:09:09.160 align:middle line:84%
Although he's very into
crystals right now,

00:09:09.160 --> 00:09:11.140 align:middle line:90%
and he's studying them.

00:09:11.140 --> 00:09:12.730 align:middle line:84%
I've given him a
lot of crystals.

00:09:12.730 --> 00:09:14.410 align:middle line:90%
He's learning about them.

00:09:14.410 --> 00:09:17.440 align:middle line:90%
But no, he's the pool man.

00:09:17.440 --> 00:09:18.590 align:middle line:90%
He mows the lawn.

00:09:18.590 --> 00:09:19.570 align:middle line:90%
He fixes everything.

00:09:19.570 --> 00:09:20.650 align:middle line:90%
He takes care of stuff.

00:09:20.650 --> 00:09:21.520 align:middle line:90%
He's very romantic.

00:09:21.520 --> 00:09:22.360 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: He plays the piano.

00:09:22.360 --> 00:09:24.485 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTENSON: Plays the
piano, writes me love songs.

00:09:24.485 --> 00:09:26.470 align:middle line:84%
But no, he's not
into all the stuff.

00:09:26.470 --> 00:09:30.130 align:middle line:84%
But as the years have gone
by, I read Tarot cards now,

00:09:30.130 --> 00:09:31.160 align:middle line:90%
which he was against--

00:09:31.160 --> 00:09:32.710 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: You dabble
with the Ouija board.

00:09:32.710 --> 00:09:33.280 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTENSON: Oh, no.

00:09:33.280 --> 00:09:35.072 align:middle line:84%
You're not going to
bring that one up, huh?

00:09:35.072 --> 00:09:37.420 align:middle line:90%
No, you know what?

00:09:37.420 --> 00:09:40.990 align:middle line:84%
I don't use the Ouija, but I do
like the talking board, which

00:09:40.990 --> 00:09:42.747 align:middle line:84%
the Ouija has that
brand, you know?

00:09:42.747 --> 00:09:43.580 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Absolutely.

00:09:43.580 --> 00:09:44.080 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTENSON: Yeah, yeah.

00:09:44.080 --> 00:09:45.910 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Is it fun to
find the right partner?

00:09:45.910 --> 00:09:46.840 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTENSON: Is it
fun for me to find

00:09:46.840 --> 00:09:47.800 align:middle line:90%
the right partner for people?

00:09:47.800 --> 00:09:48.130 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Yeah.

00:09:48.130 --> 00:09:48.930 align:middle line:90%
You enjoy that?

00:09:48.930 --> 00:09:51.680 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTENSON: Well, me and
my business partner Fredly,

00:09:51.680 --> 00:09:53.770 align:middle line:84%
we'll start doing what
we call a happy dance.

00:09:53.770 --> 00:09:57.220 align:middle line:84%
If we make a match and they're
in love or they're exclusive,

00:09:57.220 --> 00:09:58.330 align:middle line:90%
we're like, happy dance.

00:09:58.330 --> 00:10:00.520 align:middle line:84%
We turn on some music and
we dance and celebrate.

00:10:00.520 --> 00:10:01.937 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What are
the demographics

00:10:01.937 --> 00:10:04.030 align:middle line:90%
of people looking for love?

00:10:04.030 --> 00:10:05.980 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTENSON: For us in
our business lately,

00:10:05.980 --> 00:10:09.580 align:middle line:84%
it's really been the
men are mid 50s and up.

00:10:09.580 --> 00:10:11.630 align:middle line:90%
60s, 70s.

00:10:11.630 --> 00:10:14.290 align:middle line:84%
We have a couple younger
guys, but it's really mostly

00:10:14.290 --> 00:10:15.670 align:middle line:90%
been the older guys.

00:10:15.670 --> 00:10:17.140 align:middle line:90%
And I like helping those guys.

00:10:17.140 --> 00:10:21.490 align:middle line:84%
Those are guys who are divorced
or maybe even never married.

00:10:21.490 --> 00:10:23.290 align:middle line:90%
But I do like that demographic.

00:10:23.290 --> 00:10:25.570 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: I was in St.
Louis over the week,

00:10:25.570 --> 00:10:30.280 align:middle line:84%
and I'm looking outside of
the window of a restaurant

00:10:30.280 --> 00:10:32.770 align:middle line:84%
on the patio, and I
see a guy that I'm

00:10:32.770 --> 00:10:35.230 align:middle line:84%
sure I knew because I
used to work with him.

00:10:35.230 --> 00:10:39.760 align:middle line:84%
He was my CPA years
and years ago.

00:10:39.760 --> 00:10:43.600 align:middle line:84%
And I'm looking at him and
I'm going, is that Oscar?

00:10:43.600 --> 00:10:45.530 align:middle line:84%
And I sent a couple
waitresses out.

00:10:45.530 --> 00:10:47.650 align:middle line:84%
They were afraid to
say, are you Oscar?

00:10:47.650 --> 00:10:49.810 align:middle line:90%
But he was with an older lady.

00:10:49.810 --> 00:10:52.810 align:middle line:84%
And so I went outside and I
look at him and I'm saying,

00:10:52.810 --> 00:10:55.600 align:middle line:84%
sure enough, that's
him 20 years later.

00:10:55.600 --> 00:10:57.340 align:middle line:84%
It's been 20 years
since I've known him.

00:10:57.340 --> 00:10:59.170 align:middle line:90%
I went, Oscar?

00:10:59.170 --> 00:11:01.840 align:middle line:90%
Then he went, George!

00:11:01.840 --> 00:11:03.280 align:middle line:90%
It was him.

00:11:03.280 --> 00:11:07.840 align:middle line:84%
He's 93 years old
and he was on a date

00:11:07.840 --> 00:11:10.780 align:middle line:84%
with a woman who
was in her late 70s.

00:11:10.780 --> 00:11:12.320 align:middle line:84%
And they were
having a good time.

00:11:12.320 --> 00:11:13.120 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTENSON: Yeah.

00:11:13.120 --> 00:11:15.340 align:middle line:84%
I think that's important
as people get older,

00:11:15.340 --> 00:11:16.480 align:middle line:90%
not to shut yourself off.

00:11:16.480 --> 00:11:17.845 align:middle line:90%
Go ahead and go on a date.

00:11:17.845 --> 00:11:20.080 align:middle line:90%
Have a lovely meal.

00:11:20.080 --> 00:11:21.068 align:middle line:90%
It's never too late.

00:11:21.068 --> 00:11:22.610 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What are
people looking for?

00:11:22.610 --> 00:11:25.460 align:middle line:84%
Are they looking
for a relationship?

00:11:25.460 --> 00:11:27.520 align:middle line:84%
Are they looking
for companionship?

00:11:27.520 --> 00:11:28.320 align:middle line:90%
What do they need?

00:11:28.320 --> 00:11:29.862 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTENSON: Well,
with our business,

00:11:29.862 --> 00:11:31.540 align:middle line:84%
we only take on
people who are looking

00:11:31.540 --> 00:11:33.340 align:middle line:84%
for a long-term
relationship or marriage.

00:11:33.340 --> 00:11:35.620 align:middle line:84%
So we're not just a
hookup or dating service.

00:11:35.620 --> 00:11:36.460 align:middle line:90%
It's really serious.

00:11:36.460 --> 00:11:39.080 align:middle line:84%
So everybody who comes to
us does want that soul mate

00:11:39.080 --> 00:11:39.880 align:middle line:90%
connection.

00:11:39.880 --> 00:11:41.620 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What percent
of people want that?

00:11:41.620 --> 00:11:42.995 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTENSON: I
think most people.

00:11:42.995 --> 00:11:45.370 align:middle line:84%
Especially women, because
the guys will say,

00:11:45.370 --> 00:11:47.080 align:middle line:90%
are your women serious?

00:11:47.080 --> 00:11:50.800 align:middle line:84%
What woman doesn't want her
prince coming on a white horse?

00:11:50.800 --> 00:11:52.330 align:middle line:84%
I mean, really in
our heart, we're

00:11:52.330 --> 00:11:54.820 align:middle line:84%
not really-- the women
don't tend to be wanting

00:11:54.820 --> 00:11:55.990 align:middle line:90%
to juggle all these men.

00:11:55.990 --> 00:11:58.000 align:middle line:84%
They really want to
find that right person.

00:11:58.000 --> 00:11:59.800 align:middle line:84%
Now the men, however,
maybe they've

00:11:59.800 --> 00:12:00.960 align:middle line:90%
had a divorce or something.

00:12:00.960 --> 00:12:02.200 align:middle line:84%
Then they kind of want
to test the waters

00:12:02.200 --> 00:12:03.140 align:middle line:90%
and go have some fun.

00:12:03.140 --> 00:12:03.850 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Yeah, they're
a little leery.

00:12:03.850 --> 00:12:04.660 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTENSON: A little more.

00:12:04.660 --> 00:12:05.460 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:12:05.460 --> 00:12:10.253 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And do you push them
basically into going out?

00:12:10.253 --> 00:12:12.170 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTENSON: Well, if
they come to us and pay,

00:12:12.170 --> 00:12:13.700 align:middle line:84%
that means they're
ready and they want to.

00:12:13.700 --> 00:12:15.070 align:middle line:90%
But sometimes they'll think.

00:12:15.070 --> 00:12:15.320 align:middle line:90%
They--

00:12:15.320 --> 00:12:16.820 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Do they
reject what you pick?

00:12:16.820 --> 00:12:17.330 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTENSON: Yes.

00:12:17.330 --> 00:12:18.260 align:middle line:90%
Sometimes they will.

00:12:18.260 --> 00:12:18.770 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: They do?

00:12:18.770 --> 00:12:19.570 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTENSON: Yeah.

00:12:19.570 --> 00:12:20.480 align:middle line:90%
Oh, I've had guys--

00:12:20.480 --> 00:12:21.470 align:middle line:90%
I have a guy right now.

00:12:21.470 --> 00:12:24.470 align:middle line:84%
He's rejected 28
of my selections.

00:12:24.470 --> 00:12:25.350 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: 28?

00:12:25.350 --> 00:12:26.030 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTENSON: 28.

00:12:26.030 --> 00:12:27.030 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Has he
accepted any of them?

00:12:27.030 --> 00:12:27.863 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTENSON: He has.

00:12:27.863 --> 00:12:31.010 align:middle line:84%
He's met about eight
and he's rejected 20--

00:12:31.010 --> 00:12:33.140 align:middle line:84%
because they have
to see the photo.

00:12:33.140 --> 00:12:35.150 align:middle line:90%
And they're so darned visual.

00:12:35.150 --> 00:12:36.625 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS] I wish I could--

00:12:36.625 --> 00:12:38.000 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: But people
are that way.

00:12:38.000 --> 00:12:38.850 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTENSON: People
are that way.

00:12:38.850 --> 00:12:40.430 align:middle line:84%
So you just keep
going, you know?

00:12:40.430 --> 00:12:41.638 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: People are that way.

00:12:41.638 --> 00:12:44.870 align:middle line:84%
Of the eight he ended up
meeting or going out with,

00:12:44.870 --> 00:12:48.135 align:middle line:90%
how many has he seen since then?

00:12:48.135 --> 00:12:49.760 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTENSON: I'm
still looking for him.

00:12:49.760 --> 00:12:51.110 align:middle line:90%
He's very specific.

00:12:51.110 --> 00:12:54.020 align:middle line:84%
I mean, some of the guys that
I take on are so specific.

00:12:54.020 --> 00:12:57.810 align:middle line:84%
I mean, sometimes I say, I'm
a matchmaker, not a magician,

00:12:57.810 --> 00:12:58.610 align:middle line:90%
you know?

00:12:58.610 --> 00:13:00.470 align:middle line:90%
I'm doing my best.

00:13:00.470 --> 00:13:02.690 align:middle line:84%
And then other guys are
so easy, and they end up

00:13:02.690 --> 00:13:04.230 align:middle line:90%
in a relationship right away.

00:13:04.230 --> 00:13:08.180 align:middle line:84%
So it really depends on what
roadblocks they're putting up.

00:13:08.180 --> 00:13:11.300 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes guys think I really
want to date a supermodel.

00:13:11.300 --> 00:13:14.420 align:middle line:84%
They'll send me a name
of an Instagram girl

00:13:14.420 --> 00:13:16.640 align:middle line:84%
who has a million followers
or a model and say,

00:13:16.640 --> 00:13:18.560 align:middle line:90%
can you track her down for me?

00:13:18.560 --> 00:13:21.555 align:middle line:84%
One time a guy sent me a
picture of a model and said,

00:13:21.555 --> 00:13:23.180 align:middle line:84%
do you think you
could find her for me?

00:13:23.180 --> 00:13:24.150 align:middle line:90%
And maybe I'd like to date her.

00:13:24.150 --> 00:13:25.010 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Find that model?

00:13:25.010 --> 00:13:25.700 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTENSON: That person.

00:13:25.700 --> 00:13:27.200 align:middle line:84%
And I looked at
her and I said, I

00:13:27.200 --> 00:13:29.460 align:middle line:84%
think she's dating Leonardo
DiCaprio right now.

00:13:29.460 --> 00:13:30.260 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Really?

00:13:30.260 --> 00:13:31.060 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTENSON: Yeah.

00:13:31.060 --> 00:13:34.400 align:middle line:84%
I said, I don't think you've got
really a chance with that one.

00:13:34.400 --> 00:13:35.723 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS]

00:13:35.723 --> 00:13:36.890 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: But you never know.

00:13:36.890 --> 00:13:38.180 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTENSON: You
never know, you know?

00:13:38.180 --> 00:13:38.980 align:middle line:90%
I'm not going to--

00:13:38.980 --> 00:13:41.400 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Do you
go seeking people?

00:13:41.400 --> 00:13:44.842 align:middle line:84%
I mean, how do you find
the guy and the woman?

00:13:44.842 --> 00:13:47.300 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTENSON: So the men will
come to us from word of mouth.

00:13:47.300 --> 00:13:48.680 align:middle line:84%
Some of our clients,
they'll send

00:13:48.680 --> 00:13:52.010 align:middle line:90%
their friends or various ways.

00:13:52.010 --> 00:13:54.980 align:middle line:84%
Some of them have read my
books or seen my website.

00:13:54.980 --> 00:13:58.310 align:middle line:84%
Now the women, I've been
doing it so long that-- well,

00:13:58.310 --> 00:14:00.680 align:middle line:84%
I'm still getting from
the episode I was on--

00:14:00.680 --> 00:14:02.360 align:middle line:90%
I think it was 2013 here.

00:14:02.360 --> 00:14:05.030 align:middle line:84%
I still get some ladies
contacting me from that

00:14:05.030 --> 00:14:05.850 align:middle line:90%
sometimes.

00:14:05.850 --> 00:14:07.183 align:middle line:90%
But they'll maybe read my books.

00:14:07.183 --> 00:14:08.150 align:middle line:90%
I have a podcast.

00:14:08.150 --> 00:14:10.520 align:middle line:90%
I have a YouTube show.

00:14:10.520 --> 00:14:11.660 align:middle line:90%
We have recruiters.

00:14:11.660 --> 00:14:14.390 align:middle line:84%
There's probably about a dozen
ways women will come to us.

00:14:14.390 --> 00:14:17.270 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Lisa Garr on Gaia's
program "Inspirations"

00:14:17.270 --> 00:14:21.440 align:middle line:84%
interviewed Barbara De
Angelis about people finding

00:14:21.440 --> 00:14:24.110 align:middle line:90%
the way they wanted to love.

00:14:24.110 --> 00:14:27.680 align:middle line:84%
>>BARBARA DE ANGELIS: Being
in pain, having regret, being

00:14:27.680 --> 00:14:31.460 align:middle line:84%
angry, feeling
disappointed have nothing

00:14:31.460 --> 00:14:34.640 align:middle line:90%
to do with feeling love.

00:14:34.640 --> 00:14:36.680 align:middle line:84%
So many times in our
life-- and all of us

00:14:36.680 --> 00:14:38.690 align:middle line:84%
have gone through this,
from the time we first

00:14:38.690 --> 00:14:40.640 align:middle line:84%
get hurt as a child,
something happens,

00:14:40.640 --> 00:14:43.670 align:middle line:84%
someone disappoints us, someone
hurts us or doesn't love us

00:14:43.670 --> 00:14:45.210 align:middle line:90%
the way we think they should.

00:14:45.210 --> 00:14:49.250 align:middle line:84%
And we end up in a sense
freezing a piece of our heart,

00:14:49.250 --> 00:14:50.670 align:middle line:84%
freezing a piece
of our emotions.

00:14:50.670 --> 00:14:52.070 align:middle line:90%
So it's like a block of ice.

00:14:52.070 --> 00:14:55.010 align:middle line:84%
Something else happens and
there's another block of ice.

00:14:55.010 --> 00:14:58.100 align:middle line:84%
Bit by bit, block
by block, we end up

00:14:58.100 --> 00:15:00.830 align:middle line:84%
with frozen ice walls
around our heart.

00:15:00.830 --> 00:15:02.330 align:middle line:90%
Our love can't get out.

00:15:02.330 --> 00:15:04.490 align:middle line:90%
Other people's can't get in.

00:15:04.490 --> 00:15:05.840 align:middle line:90%
But it's there.

00:15:05.840 --> 00:15:08.000 align:middle line:84%
Just like water
doesn't disappear,

00:15:08.000 --> 00:15:11.040 align:middle line:84%
H2O doesn't disappear when
it's in the form of ice,

00:15:11.040 --> 00:15:12.188 align:middle line:90%
it's the same substance.

00:15:12.188 --> 00:15:13.355 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA GARR: Different form.

00:15:13.355 --> 00:15:14.897 align:middle line:84%
>>DE ANGELIS: --but
it needs to melt.

00:15:14.897 --> 00:15:17.442 align:middle line:84%
Love can take the form
of resistance, of anger,

00:15:17.442 --> 00:15:18.650 align:middle line:90%
of being shut off, et cetera.

00:15:18.650 --> 00:15:23.840 align:middle line:84%
So choosing to love, meaning
to feel the love, even

00:15:23.840 --> 00:15:26.270 align:middle line:84%
when we're hurt, even
when we're disappointed

00:15:26.270 --> 00:15:28.100 align:middle line:84%
is one of the great
spiritual choices.

00:15:28.100 --> 00:15:30.380 align:middle line:84%
That doesn't mean you choose
to let somebody hurt you

00:15:30.380 --> 00:15:32.240 align:middle line:90%
or you even stay with someone.

00:15:32.240 --> 00:15:35.630 align:middle line:84%
But to sacrifice
our own lovingness.

00:15:35.630 --> 00:15:37.625 align:middle line:84%
And a lot of people
watching have done that.

00:15:37.625 --> 00:15:38.750 align:middle line:90%
They can go, you know what?

00:15:38.750 --> 00:15:42.450 align:middle line:84%
Ever since this happened, I've
been afraid to love again,

00:15:42.450 --> 00:15:43.590 align:middle line:90%
et cetera, et cetera.

00:15:43.590 --> 00:15:45.650 align:middle line:84%
But that love is
what nourishes us.

00:15:45.650 --> 00:15:49.100 align:middle line:84%
Love in the form
of our heart energy

00:15:49.100 --> 00:15:50.420 align:middle line:90%
is the form of relationship.

00:15:50.420 --> 00:15:54.290 align:middle line:84%
In the form of energy up
here, it's creativity.

00:15:54.290 --> 00:15:57.080 align:middle line:90%
That source makes us juicy.

00:15:57.080 --> 00:15:59.160 align:middle line:90%
It makes us flow in life.

00:15:59.160 --> 00:16:00.920 align:middle line:84%
And so many people
need to go through what

00:16:00.920 --> 00:16:03.380 align:middle line:84%
I call the big melt,
because they've

00:16:03.380 --> 00:16:05.420 align:middle line:90%
gotten crusty and frozen.

00:16:05.420 --> 00:16:07.760 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: What is the big melt?

00:16:07.760 --> 00:16:10.160 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTENSON: A melting that--

00:16:10.160 --> 00:16:11.760 align:middle line:90%
ice around the heart--

00:16:11.760 --> 00:16:13.010 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Or a melting of love?

00:16:13.010 --> 00:16:15.800 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTENSON: I think
it's a melting into love.

00:16:15.800 --> 00:16:19.790 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, a lot of people will say,
well, my last relationship,

00:16:19.790 --> 00:16:21.560 align:middle line:84%
I found out the person
was an alcoholic

00:16:21.560 --> 00:16:22.580 align:middle line:90%
or they cheated on me.

00:16:22.580 --> 00:16:23.380 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Or a narcissist.

00:16:23.380 --> 00:16:24.588 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTENSON: Or a narcissist.

00:16:24.588 --> 00:16:26.900 align:middle line:84%
That's a big thing
nowadays, the narcissist.

00:16:26.900 --> 00:16:29.780 align:middle line:84%
So then they're afraid to get
into a relationship again.

00:16:29.780 --> 00:16:32.090 align:middle line:84%
But that's where you kind
of go back and look at maybe

00:16:32.090 --> 00:16:33.590 align:middle line:90%
some childhood patterns.

00:16:33.590 --> 00:16:35.540 align:middle line:84%
For example, let's
say you were a child

00:16:35.540 --> 00:16:38.050 align:middle line:84%
and your parents argued all the
time, and it was just very--

00:16:38.050 --> 00:16:38.840 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: And you witnessed that.

00:16:38.840 --> 00:16:40.257 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTENSON: And
you witnessed it,

00:16:40.257 --> 00:16:42.470 align:middle line:84%
or maybe there was even
some physical altercations.

00:16:42.470 --> 00:16:44.540 align:middle line:84%
And then in the back of
your subconscious, you're

00:16:44.540 --> 00:16:47.780 align:middle line:84%
thinking, well, being in a
relationship, being married's

00:16:47.780 --> 00:16:48.610 align:middle line:90%
dangerous.

00:16:48.610 --> 00:16:49.410 align:middle line:90%
It's scary.

00:16:49.410 --> 00:16:50.390 align:middle line:90%
It's not fun.

00:16:50.390 --> 00:16:52.010 align:middle line:90%
It's dramatic.

00:16:52.010 --> 00:16:53.628 align:middle line:84%
When you get older
and you're looking,

00:16:53.628 --> 00:16:55.670 align:middle line:84%
you think, oh, yeah, well,
I want a relationship.

00:16:55.670 --> 00:16:58.130 align:middle line:90%
I'm online.

00:16:58.130 --> 00:17:00.170 align:middle line:84%
I've hired a
matchmaker, whatever.

00:17:00.170 --> 00:17:02.690 align:middle line:84%
So you say, you maybe think
you want a relationship,

00:17:02.690 --> 00:17:05.089 align:middle line:84%
but that program's
running in the background.

00:17:05.089 --> 00:17:06.020 align:middle line:90%
Oh, no.

00:17:06.020 --> 00:17:07.010 align:middle line:90%
It's not safe.

00:17:07.010 --> 00:17:10.730 align:middle line:84%
So then you'll pick
unavailable people.

00:17:10.730 --> 00:17:13.310 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Marla, let's talk a
little bit about obsessions,

00:17:13.310 --> 00:17:17.839 align:middle line:84%
because I have known
people who become obsessed

00:17:17.839 --> 00:17:18.763 align:middle line:90%
with the other person.

00:17:18.763 --> 00:17:19.680 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTENSON: Oh, yeah.

00:17:19.680 --> 00:17:22.640 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And that's not
healthy for both people.

00:17:22.640 --> 00:17:23.930 align:middle line:90%
What causes that?

00:17:23.930 --> 00:17:25.350 align:middle line:90%
Is it an insecurity?

00:17:25.350 --> 00:17:26.150 align:middle line:90%
What is it?

00:17:26.150 --> 00:17:27.020 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTENSON: Yes.

00:17:27.020 --> 00:17:28.670 align:middle line:90%
We've got to work on self-love.

00:17:28.670 --> 00:17:30.890 align:middle line:84%
It's those patterns
from childhood.

00:17:30.890 --> 00:17:32.920 align:middle line:84%
Everybody-- anybody
you talk to will

00:17:32.920 --> 00:17:34.670 align:middle line:84%
have something that
happened in childhood,

00:17:34.670 --> 00:17:39.340 align:middle line:84%
whether they were bullied
or maybe they were abused

00:17:39.340 --> 00:17:40.140 align:middle line:90%
or something.

00:17:40.140 --> 00:17:41.750 align:middle line:90%
So it's that codependence.

00:17:41.750 --> 00:17:43.910 align:middle line:84%
They're kind of
glomming on to someone.

00:17:43.910 --> 00:17:46.220 align:middle line:90%
And I do readings too.

00:17:46.220 --> 00:17:48.110 align:middle line:84%
I work on a couple of
psychic hotlines now,

00:17:48.110 --> 00:17:49.280 align:middle line:90%
George, for fun, you know?

00:17:49.280 --> 00:17:51.920 align:middle line:84%
And I get a lot of calls
from women who want to know,

00:17:51.920 --> 00:17:53.240 align:middle line:90%
is my ex coming back?

00:17:53.240 --> 00:17:54.240 align:middle line:90%
Is he thinking about me?

00:17:54.240 --> 00:17:55.020 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Do they want him?

00:17:55.020 --> 00:17:56.353 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTENSON: They want him back.

00:17:56.353 --> 00:17:59.000 align:middle line:84%
I never knew so many women
were wanting their exes back,

00:17:59.000 --> 00:18:01.100 align:middle line:84%
even if he's with somebody--
he had cheated on her

00:18:01.100 --> 00:18:02.267 align:middle line:90%
and gone with somebody else.

00:18:02.267 --> 00:18:04.280 align:middle line:84%
And they still call
me and say, but do you

00:18:04.280 --> 00:18:05.900 align:middle line:90%
think he'll come back?

00:18:05.900 --> 00:18:10.280 align:middle line:84%
And so we do some cord cutting,
those energetic cords, energy

00:18:10.280 --> 00:18:12.530 align:middle line:84%
work, because we have
cords that are attached,

00:18:12.530 --> 00:18:15.920 align:middle line:84%
especially if we've been
intimate, that attach us.

00:18:15.920 --> 00:18:18.080 align:middle line:84%
It's that if you
think about when

00:18:18.080 --> 00:18:21.160 align:middle line:84%
you're thinking about somebody
and then they call, you know?

00:18:21.160 --> 00:18:22.710 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: I love
that, that intuition.

00:18:22.710 --> 00:18:23.510 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTENSON: Yeah.

00:18:23.510 --> 00:18:27.260 align:middle line:84%
Well, that's because we have
cords attached to us that form.

00:18:27.260 --> 00:18:29.810 align:middle line:84%
So I take them through
a cord cutting.

00:18:29.810 --> 00:18:32.423 align:middle line:84%
I call in Archangel Michael and
cut those cords and release.

00:18:32.423 --> 00:18:34.340 align:middle line:84%
They've got to do some
releasing work and then

00:18:34.340 --> 00:18:36.680 align:middle line:84%
some self-love work
and maybe some energy

00:18:36.680 --> 00:18:39.900 align:middle line:84%
healing and self-esteem
work and boundary work.

00:18:39.900 --> 00:18:40.700 align:middle line:90%
All of that.

00:18:40.700 --> 00:18:43.250 align:middle line:84%
But some people don't want
to do the work on themselves.

00:18:43.250 --> 00:18:45.060 align:middle line:84%
They just want to
call a psychic.

00:18:45.060 --> 00:18:46.910 align:middle line:84%
When's the person
coming in my life?

00:18:46.910 --> 00:18:49.517 align:middle line:84%
One person even asked, I want
to know what my future husband's

00:18:49.517 --> 00:18:51.350 align:middle line:84%
name is, what he looks
like, where he lives,

00:18:51.350 --> 00:18:52.100 align:middle line:90%
and how old he is.

00:18:52.100 --> 00:18:52.610 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Ha.

00:18:52.610 --> 00:18:54.777 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTENSON: And then I
said, well, I'm not Kreskin.

00:18:54.777 --> 00:18:57.200 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS] I don't know.

00:18:57.200 --> 00:19:00.570 align:middle line:84%
But do the work on yourself,
because frequency is always

00:19:00.570 --> 00:19:01.370 align:middle line:90%
matched.

00:19:01.370 --> 00:19:02.910 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Well, you
make people happy.

00:19:02.910 --> 00:19:03.980 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTENSON: I
make people-- yeah.

00:19:03.980 --> 00:19:05.522 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And do they
come back to you

00:19:05.522 --> 00:19:09.167 align:middle line:84%
after the fact, either
couple, and thank you?

00:19:09.167 --> 00:19:11.000 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTENSON: Sometimes,
and then sometimes I

00:19:11.000 --> 00:19:13.692 align:middle line:84%
find out through the grapevine
that they got married

00:19:13.692 --> 00:19:14.900 align:middle line:90%
and went off into the sunset.

00:19:14.900 --> 00:19:15.990 align:middle line:90%
I never even knew about it.

00:19:15.990 --> 00:19:16.850 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: They never told you?

00:19:16.850 --> 00:19:17.480 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTENSON: No.

00:19:17.480 --> 00:19:18.140 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Why not?

00:19:18.140 --> 00:19:19.340 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTENSON: I think--
you know what I think?

00:19:19.340 --> 00:19:21.560 align:middle line:84%
They're just so happy in
their life, they just--

00:19:21.560 --> 00:19:22.620 align:middle line:90%
and that's fine.

00:19:22.620 --> 00:19:24.020 align:middle line:90%
I don't need the thanks.

00:19:24.020 --> 00:19:26.150 align:middle line:84%
I'm just happy that
I was able to do it.

00:19:26.150 --> 00:19:28.400 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Well, you know,
you're an enlightened person.

00:19:28.400 --> 00:19:30.320 align:middle line:90%
I've known you for years.

00:19:30.320 --> 00:19:32.045 align:middle line:84%
You're the Beverly
Hills matchmaker.

00:19:32.045 --> 00:19:33.080 align:middle line:90%
That was your first--

00:19:33.080 --> 00:19:34.190 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTENSON: Well,
now my moniker--

00:19:34.190 --> 00:19:35.648 align:middle line:84%
I was the Beverly
Hills matchmaker.

00:19:35.648 --> 00:19:37.520 align:middle line:84%
Now I moved to the
Valley, and now I

00:19:37.520 --> 00:19:39.020 align:middle line:84%
call myself the
mystical matchmaker.

00:19:39.020 --> 00:19:40.380 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: I love it.

00:19:40.380 --> 00:19:41.330 align:middle line:90%
I love it.

00:19:41.330 --> 00:19:43.070 align:middle line:84%
What is it about
matchmaking that

00:19:43.070 --> 00:19:45.110 align:middle line:90%
is satisfying for you, Marla?

00:19:45.110 --> 00:19:47.660 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTENSON: Well, I get to
meet so many amazing people

00:19:47.660 --> 00:19:51.620 align:middle line:84%
from all different backgrounds,
and what they're doing

00:19:51.620 --> 00:19:52.640 align:middle line:90%
is so interesting.

00:19:52.640 --> 00:19:55.610 align:middle line:84%
And then just helping them
find that special person.

00:19:55.610 --> 00:19:56.670 align:middle line:90%
Everybody wants love.

00:19:56.670 --> 00:19:59.625 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Have you rejected
paying clients before?

00:19:59.625 --> 00:20:00.500 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTENSON: Oh, yes.

00:20:00.500 --> 00:20:00.950 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: You do?

00:20:00.950 --> 00:20:01.340 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTENSON: Yeah.

00:20:01.340 --> 00:20:02.673 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Why do you reject them?

00:20:02.673 --> 00:20:05.070 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTENSON: Well, if
they're too out of reality.

00:20:05.070 --> 00:20:07.590 align:middle line:84%
So let's say a guy's
65 and he says, look,

00:20:07.590 --> 00:20:12.515 align:middle line:84%
I don't want to date anyone over
30, or he has too many things--

00:20:12.515 --> 00:20:14.140 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: His goals
are way out of line.

00:20:14.140 --> 00:20:14.510 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTENSON: Yeah.

00:20:14.510 --> 00:20:16.400 align:middle line:84%
We'll say, look, we
can't do-- it's too hard

00:20:16.400 --> 00:20:17.352 align:middle line:90%
or it's not realistic.

00:20:17.352 --> 00:20:19.310 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Are they depressed
when they walk out?

00:20:19.310 --> 00:20:20.303 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTENSON: No.

00:20:20.303 --> 00:20:22.220 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes a guy will
say, you're rejecting me?

00:20:22.220 --> 00:20:22.985 align:middle line:90%
I want to-- you know--

00:20:22.985 --> 00:20:24.110 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: I've got the cash.

00:20:24.110 --> 00:20:25.020 align:middle line:90%
I'm ready to go.

00:20:25.020 --> 00:20:26.340 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTENSON: But if
we can't help them,

00:20:26.340 --> 00:20:28.465 align:middle line:84%
then they're going to want
their money back anyway.

00:20:28.465 --> 00:20:29.960 align:middle line:84%
I won't be able
to sleep at night.

00:20:29.960 --> 00:20:32.280 align:middle line:84%
If I can't help him, I
don't want to take him on.

00:20:32.280 --> 00:20:33.080 align:middle line:90%
It's too hard.

00:20:33.080 --> 00:20:36.380 align:middle line:84%
I only want to take on
people that I can potentially

00:20:36.380 --> 00:20:37.530 align:middle line:90%
get into a relationship.

00:20:37.530 --> 00:20:39.380 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: "The Buddha
Made Me Do it."

00:20:39.380 --> 00:20:40.580 align:middle line:90%
Tell me about that.

00:20:40.580 --> 00:20:42.205 align:middle line:10%
>>MARTENSON: "The
Buddha Made Me Do it:

00:20:42.205 --> 00:20:45.350 align:middle line:10%
A Field Guide to EnLITEnment,"
is my spiritual memoir.

00:20:45.350 --> 00:20:46.700 align:middle line:10%
And that was--

00:20:46.700 --> 00:20:49.460 align:middle line:10%
I had written a couple of
other memoirs before that.

00:20:49.460 --> 00:20:53.163 align:middle line:84%
And Adolfo and I had moved
into a house from Hollywood.

00:20:53.163 --> 00:20:54.080 align:middle line:90%
We went to the Valley.

00:20:54.080 --> 00:20:56.000 align:middle line:84%
And I had this little
Buddha statuette

00:20:56.000 --> 00:20:57.200 align:middle line:90%
that somebody had given me.

00:20:57.200 --> 00:20:58.100 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: A big belly.

00:20:58.100 --> 00:21:00.517 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTENSON: Well, it was the
little one, like-- you know.

00:21:00.517 --> 00:21:02.060 align:middle line:90%
And it was made of wood.

00:21:02.060 --> 00:21:05.190 align:middle line:84%
And I was decluttering,
and I got rid of it.

00:21:05.190 --> 00:21:06.380 align:middle line:90%
It wasn't even Adolfo's.

00:21:06.380 --> 00:21:08.750 align:middle line:84%
But he said, hey, Marla, where
is that Buddha statue at?

00:21:08.750 --> 00:21:09.860 align:middle line:90%
What happened to it?

00:21:09.860 --> 00:21:10.950 align:middle line:90%
Did you get rid of it?

00:21:10.950 --> 00:21:12.240 align:middle line:84%
You better not have
gotten rid of it.

00:21:12.240 --> 00:21:14.698 align:middle line:84%
That's just like you to get
rid of stuff without asking me.

00:21:14.698 --> 00:21:17.270 align:middle line:84%
And I was like, I'm not
going to admit that I--

00:21:17.270 --> 00:21:19.070 align:middle line:84%
I think it's probably
in the garage packed.

00:21:19.070 --> 00:21:19.870 align:middle line:90%
I'll find it.

00:21:19.870 --> 00:21:21.893 align:middle line:84%
I started driving around
to all the spiritual--

00:21:21.893 --> 00:21:23.060 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: To find the Buddha.

00:21:23.060 --> 00:21:24.768 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTENSON: To replace
it, the same one.

00:21:24.768 --> 00:21:26.650 align:middle line:84%
And I went to all these
spiritual hotspots.

00:21:26.650 --> 00:21:28.100 align:middle line:90%
Couldn't find it.

00:21:28.100 --> 00:21:30.990 align:middle line:84%
He kept asking about it, so
I went to one last place.

00:21:30.990 --> 00:21:32.840 align:middle line:84%
And they didn't have
a Buddha, but they

00:21:32.840 --> 00:21:36.110 align:middle line:84%
had classes every
Wednesday night

00:21:36.110 --> 00:21:38.990 align:middle line:84%
on connecting with your
guides, crystal healing,

00:21:38.990 --> 00:21:40.520 align:middle line:90%
opening your intuition.

00:21:40.520 --> 00:21:42.650 align:middle line:84%
And I called my friend
Julie and I said, hey,

00:21:42.650 --> 00:21:43.790 align:middle line:90%
I didn't find any Buddhas.

00:21:43.790 --> 00:21:46.080 align:middle line:84%
She was my BFF
that lived nearby.

00:21:46.080 --> 00:21:48.060 align:middle line:84%
And I said, hey, do you
want to take a class?

00:21:48.060 --> 00:21:50.540 align:middle line:90%
We started taking these classes.

00:21:50.540 --> 00:21:52.730 align:middle line:84%
We got so hooked,
George, that we started

00:21:52.730 --> 00:21:54.200 align:middle line:90%
taking classes all over town.

00:21:54.200 --> 00:21:57.500 align:middle line:84%
And pendulums and
candle magic, and I

00:21:57.500 --> 00:22:00.690 align:middle line:84%
became a Reiki practitioner
and crystal healer.

00:22:00.690 --> 00:22:01.970 align:middle line:90%
And I was deep diving.

00:22:01.970 --> 00:22:03.650 align:middle line:84%
And Adolfo's like,
what's going on?

00:22:03.650 --> 00:22:07.100 align:middle line:84%
[LAUGHS] And I've been
taking it further.

00:22:07.100 --> 00:22:08.480 align:middle line:90%
