infuse that excitement

00:29:27.510 --> 00:29:29.010 align:middle line:90%
and love again into their life.

00:29:29.010 --> 00:29:30.888 align:middle line:90%
So I really enjoy it.

00:29:30.888 --> 00:29:33.180 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What has been the
most magical moment for you?

00:29:33.180 --> 00:29:35.520 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTENSON: Oh, the most
magical moment was connecting

00:29:35.520 --> 00:29:40.650 align:middle line:84%
with that channeler who
channels Red Eagle and talking--

00:29:40.650 --> 00:29:42.660 align:middle line:90%
actually talking to this spirit.

00:29:42.660 --> 00:29:46.650 align:middle line:84%
I'm real big into channelers,
because thinking about talking

00:29:46.650 --> 00:29:48.990 align:middle line:84%
to an entity that's coming
through that's in a different

00:29:48.990 --> 00:29:52.030 align:middle line:84%
dimension or an ET or
something-- like, you know,

00:29:52.030 --> 00:29:52.830 align:middle line:90%
there's--

00:29:52.830 --> 00:29:53.940 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Are you a channeler?

00:29:53.940 --> 00:29:55.080 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTENSON: Well,
I channel my--

00:29:55.080 --> 00:29:55.880 align:middle line:90%
in a certain way.

00:29:55.880 --> 00:29:57.210 align:middle line:90%
I channel my angel, Thomas.

00:29:57.210 --> 00:29:59.100 align:middle line:84%
He's a guide, and I
can bring him through.

00:29:59.100 --> 00:29:59.460 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Thomas?

00:29:59.460 --> 00:30:00.810 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTENSON: Yeah,
his name's Thomas.

00:30:00.810 --> 00:30:01.830 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Just like my producer.

00:30:01.830 --> 00:30:02.430 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTENSON: I know.

00:30:02.430 --> 00:30:04.270 align:middle line:84%
And I don't call him
Tommy, but Thomas.

00:30:04.270 --> 00:30:05.460 align:middle line:90%
But I do get messages.

00:30:05.460 --> 00:30:07.200 align:middle line:84%
I've given a lot of
messages from Thomas.

00:30:07.200 --> 00:30:08.582 align:middle line:90%
And people say that--

00:30:08.582 --> 00:30:09.540 align:middle line:90%
I say, I want feedback.

00:30:09.540 --> 00:30:11.140 align:middle line:90%
And they say, it resonates.

00:30:11.140 --> 00:30:11.940 align:middle line:90%
It's true.

00:30:11.940 --> 00:30:13.560 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: How did you
know his name was Thomas?

00:30:13.560 --> 00:30:14.475 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTENSON: He said
it on the board.

00:30:14.475 --> 00:30:16.058 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS] I met him on the board.

00:30:16.058 --> 00:30:17.100 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: The Ouija board?

00:30:17.100 --> 00:30:18.180 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTENSON: Well, it's
not-- it wasn't a Ouija--

00:30:18.180 --> 00:30:19.470 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: You call
it a talking board.

00:30:19.470 --> 00:30:21.303 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTENSON: Because
it's not a brand Ouija.

00:30:21.303 --> 00:30:23.170 align:middle line:84%
It's just a board
with the alphabet.

00:30:23.170 --> 00:30:23.970 align:middle line:90%
I'm like Kar--

00:30:23.970 --> 00:30:24.210 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: But it looks
like a Ouija board.

00:30:24.210 --> 00:30:26.543 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTENSON: Hey, my girlfriend
Karen Dahlman, you know,

00:30:26.543 --> 00:30:29.420 align:middle line:84%
we always say we can write
the alphabet on a paper bag

00:30:29.420 --> 00:30:30.220 align:middle line:90%
and it'll work.

00:30:30.220 --> 00:30:32.040 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: The devil's is
going to take Karen one day,

00:30:32.040 --> 00:30:32.740 align:middle line:90%
you know that.

00:30:32.740 --> 00:30:33.540 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTENSON: No.

00:30:33.540 --> 00:30:35.600 align:middle line:84%
[LAUGHS] She's such
a wonderful gal.

00:30:35.600 --> 00:30:39.572 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: She is, but she
dabbles with the dark side.

00:30:39.572 --> 00:30:41.280 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTENSON: You think
it's dark, though,

00:30:41.280 --> 00:30:42.600 align:middle line:90%
just because it's a board, or--

00:30:42.600 --> 00:30:43.050 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: I do.

00:30:43.050 --> 00:30:44.592 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTENSON: She
does everything so--

00:30:44.592 --> 00:30:48.120 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: I think strange spirits
can come through a Ouija board.

00:30:48.120 --> 00:30:49.320 align:middle line:90%
You've got to be careful.

00:30:49.320 --> 00:30:49.810 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTENSON: Yeah.

00:30:49.810 --> 00:30:51.300 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: But she swears
by it, as you know.

00:30:51.300 --> 00:30:52.100 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTENSON: Right.

00:30:52.100 --> 00:30:54.315 align:middle line:84%
Because we're only
working with the light.

00:30:54.315 --> 00:30:55.440 align:middle line:90%
We're not thinking of that.

00:30:55.440 --> 00:30:57.990 align:middle line:84%
Now if somebody used it when
they're under the influence--

00:30:57.990 --> 00:31:01.860 align:middle line:84%
drugs, alcohol, not taking
it seriously, not treating it

00:31:01.860 --> 00:31:03.630 align:middle line:90%
respectfully-- something could.

00:31:03.630 --> 00:31:05.130 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Are you intuitive?

00:31:05.130 --> 00:31:06.935 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTENSON: Yes,
we're all intuitive.

00:31:06.935 --> 00:31:09.120 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Did any of these
practices enhance that?

00:31:09.120 --> 00:31:10.110 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTENSON: You know,
what opened me up

00:31:10.110 --> 00:31:12.152 align:middle line:84%
and the way I got to
connect with my angel Thomas

00:31:12.152 --> 00:31:15.420 align:middle line:84%
is what she was talking
about, the last clip, Reiki,

00:31:15.420 --> 00:31:17.880 align:middle line:90%
the energetic attunements.

00:31:17.880 --> 00:31:19.560 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: What exactly is Reiki?

00:31:19.560 --> 00:31:21.750 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTENSON: So it's
an energy healing

00:31:21.750 --> 00:31:23.970 align:middle line:90%
modality that comes from Japan.

00:31:23.970 --> 00:31:29.670 align:middle line:84%
And what happens is a Reiki
master will attune you

00:31:29.670 --> 00:31:30.510 align:middle line:90%
with the symbols.

00:31:30.510 --> 00:31:33.570 align:middle line:84%
They'll put the symbols
into your energy field.

00:31:33.570 --> 00:31:36.360 align:middle line:84%
And so it was so interesting,
because I'd feel immediately

00:31:36.360 --> 00:31:40.650 align:middle line:84%
when I was studying Reiki
and the buzzing in my hands,

00:31:40.650 --> 00:31:43.020 align:middle line:84%
the tingling, the
flow of the energy.

00:31:43.020 --> 00:31:45.150 align:middle line:84%
And then I had some other
energetic attachments

00:31:45.150 --> 00:31:47.700 align:middle line:84%
from different people,
and I really noticed,

00:31:47.700 --> 00:31:49.950 align:middle line:84%
that's what opened me
up to be more intuitive,

00:31:49.950 --> 00:31:52.170 align:middle line:90%
having messages come through.

00:31:52.170 --> 00:31:55.290 align:middle line:84%
Having a quiet mind and being
calm is very important too.

00:31:55.290 --> 00:31:57.510 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Have you used
these intuitive abilities

00:31:57.510 --> 00:32:00.525 align:middle line:84%
to match people or
not match people?

00:32:00.525 --> 00:32:01.680 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTENSON: A little bit.

00:32:01.680 --> 00:32:05.040 align:middle line:84%
With the matching, it's still
so much of the first things.

00:32:05.040 --> 00:32:08.100 align:middle line:84%
Location, age range,
looks, background,

00:32:08.100 --> 00:32:09.420 align:middle line:90%
now political this and that.

00:32:09.420 --> 00:32:11.463 align:middle line:84%
So it's not as much--
it's like, OK, well,

00:32:11.463 --> 00:32:13.380 align:middle line:84%
we've got everything on
paper that looks good.

00:32:13.380 --> 00:32:15.780 align:middle line:84%
Now it's up to you guys to
see if there's chemistry.

00:32:15.780 --> 00:32:17.670 align:middle line:90%
So not as much.

00:32:17.670 --> 00:32:20.160 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: But it is
an ability for you,

00:32:20.160 --> 00:32:21.780 align:middle line:90%
because you're very intuitive.

00:32:21.780 --> 00:32:23.130 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTENSON: Yeah.

00:32:23.130 --> 00:32:25.260 align:middle line:84%
I have been nurturing
that over the years.

00:32:25.260 --> 00:32:27.010 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Does everybody
have that ability?

00:32:27.010 --> 00:32:27.300 align:middle line:90%
I think so.

00:32:27.300 --> 00:32:28.467 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTENSON: Everybody does.

00:32:28.467 --> 00:32:31.780 align:middle line:84%
That's our intuition
that we're born with.

00:32:31.780 --> 00:32:33.540 align:middle line:90%
It's part of our makeup.

00:32:33.540 --> 00:32:35.130 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: On the
"Inspirations" show,

00:32:35.130 --> 00:32:37.170 align:middle line:84%
our friendly Lisa Garr
once again interviewed

00:32:37.170 --> 00:32:39.960 align:middle line:84%
a spiritual teacher,
Sonia Choquette,

00:32:39.960 --> 00:32:42.920 align:middle line:90%
about these intuitive abilities.

00:32:42.920 --> 00:32:45.410 align:middle line:84%
>>SONIA CHOQUETTE: We are
all born with a sixth sense,

00:32:45.410 --> 00:32:47.300 align:middle line:90%
because it's your heart.

00:32:47.300 --> 00:32:49.430 align:middle line:10%
It is the first
organ in your body

00:32:49.430 --> 00:32:52.220 align:middle line:10%
to develop, way
before your brain,

00:32:52.220 --> 00:32:54.410 align:middle line:10%
way before your other senses.

00:32:54.410 --> 00:32:56.540 align:middle line:10%
The second organ to
develop in your body

00:32:56.540 --> 00:32:59.030 align:middle line:10%
is the cochlear, the inner ear.

00:32:59.030 --> 00:33:04.130 align:middle line:10%
And those two pick up energy and
vibration, and that informs us.

00:33:04.130 --> 00:33:06.080 align:middle line:10%
People don't know
this, but every one

00:33:06.080 --> 00:33:10.460 align:middle line:10%
of your physical senses goes
through the ear into the heart.

00:33:10.460 --> 00:33:13.640 align:middle line:10%
So your heart is
your guidance system,

00:33:13.640 --> 00:33:16.800 align:middle line:10%
and we lose it because
we are conditioned--

00:33:16.800 --> 00:33:19.700 align:middle line:10%
the majority of the planet
has been conditioned

00:33:19.700 --> 00:33:22.640 align:middle line:10%
to ignore that inner wisdom.

00:33:22.640 --> 00:33:24.090 align:middle line:90%
But we all start out with it.

00:33:24.090 --> 00:33:24.890 align:middle line:90%
>>GARR: Hmm.

00:33:24.890 --> 00:33:27.473 align:middle line:84%
It's interesting, because if you
think about a baby in a womb,

00:33:27.473 --> 00:33:30.500 align:middle line:84%
they can pick up the
feelings of the mother.

00:33:30.500 --> 00:33:31.880 align:middle line:10%
>>CHOQUETTE: Very much so.

00:33:31.880 --> 00:33:34.220 align:middle line:10%
And they're hearing everything.

00:33:34.220 --> 00:33:35.780 align:middle line:10%
We are very conscious.

00:33:35.780 --> 00:33:42.170 align:middle line:10%
And your heart is a very
intelligent, very informing

00:33:42.170 --> 00:33:43.057 align:middle line:10%
organ.

00:33:43.057 --> 00:33:45.140 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What do you think
of this ability, Marla?

00:33:45.140 --> 00:33:45.940 align:middle line:90%
That's pretty good.

00:33:45.940 --> 00:33:47.280 align:middle line:90%
I mean, you've got that ability.

00:33:47.280 --> 00:33:47.660 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTENSON: Yeah.

00:33:47.660 --> 00:33:48.160 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: It works.

00:33:48.160 --> 00:33:49.850 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTENSON: I love
Sonia Choquette.

00:33:49.850 --> 00:33:50.970 align:middle line:90%
Her teachings are great.

00:33:50.970 --> 00:33:53.255 align:middle line:90%
And yeah, you just use it--

00:33:53.255 --> 00:33:55.130 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I wanted to be
able to give readings.

00:33:55.130 --> 00:33:57.672 align:middle line:84%
That's something I wanted to
do, because I'd see other people

00:33:57.672 --> 00:34:00.440 align:middle line:90%
doing it, and I just had that--

00:34:00.440 --> 00:34:03.125 align:middle line:84%
I did some plant
medicine journeys

00:34:03.125 --> 00:34:05.670 align:middle line:90%
over the last few years as well.

00:34:05.670 --> 00:34:07.130 align:middle line:90%
It helps open things up.

00:34:07.130 --> 00:34:08.179 align:middle line:90%
We do have the inner ear.

00:34:08.179 --> 00:34:10.670 align:middle line:84%
We have the third eye and
we have the third ear,

00:34:10.670 --> 00:34:12.820 align:middle line:84%
where we get those-- we
can hear those messages.

00:34:12.820 --> 00:34:14.510 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Do you think this
has helped your matchmaking

00:34:14.510 --> 00:34:15.508 align:middle line:90%
abilities?

00:34:15.508 --> 00:34:18.050 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTENSON: Well, it helps me
understand people a little bit

00:34:18.050 --> 00:34:20.270 align:middle line:84%
more and have more
compassion, because we all

00:34:20.270 --> 00:34:24.560 align:middle line:84%
come from a place of some
pain in the background

00:34:24.560 --> 00:34:25.460 align:middle line:90%
from our childhood.

00:34:25.460 --> 00:34:28.146 align:middle line:84%
Like I said, everybody has
something where they're--

00:34:28.146 --> 00:34:29.610 align:middle line:90%
they just want love.

00:34:29.610 --> 00:34:33.440 align:middle line:84%
And so that helps me
understand their heart.

00:34:33.440 --> 00:34:34.760 align:middle line:90%
They are energetic beings.

00:34:34.760 --> 00:34:37.820 align:middle line:84%
And looking more at the soul
instead of, well, this guy,

00:34:37.820 --> 00:34:39.920 align:middle line:84%
he's too superficial, or
he wants this or that.

00:34:39.920 --> 00:34:41.300 align:middle line:90%
It's easy to maybe get jaded.

00:34:41.300 --> 00:34:44.960 align:middle line:84%
But I just try to see them
as just a beautiful spark

00:34:44.960 --> 00:34:48.052 align:middle line:84%
of the divine who wants to
find love and express love.

00:34:48.052 --> 00:34:49.969 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Have you ever
had anybody come to you

00:34:49.969 --> 00:34:53.030 align:middle line:90%
who was just totally despondent?

00:34:53.030 --> 00:34:54.972 align:middle line:84%
(WHINY VOICE) I
can't find anybody.

00:34:54.972 --> 00:34:56.889 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTENSON: Well, they'll
say their patterns.

00:34:56.889 --> 00:35:00.170 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, I'm always
attracting the gold diggers

00:35:00.170 --> 00:35:02.780 align:middle line:84%
or the drama queens or the
high-maintenance women.

00:35:02.780 --> 00:35:04.580 align:middle line:90%
And there's something there.

00:35:04.580 --> 00:35:07.260 align:middle line:84%
I have a client who
tends to do that.

00:35:07.260 --> 00:35:09.230 align:middle line:84%
And I say, why do
you always pick

00:35:09.230 --> 00:35:11.240 align:middle line:84%
these women who just
drain you financially

00:35:11.240 --> 00:35:12.530 align:middle line:90%
or they stand you up?

00:35:12.530 --> 00:35:14.320 align:middle line:84%
And then I said,
there's something.

00:35:14.320 --> 00:35:15.870 align:middle line:84%
Why is that-- it's
working for you.

00:35:15.870 --> 00:35:16.670 align:middle line:90%
What is it?

00:35:16.670 --> 00:35:17.670 align:middle line:90%
And he thought about it.

00:35:17.670 --> 00:35:20.803 align:middle line:84%
He says, I think I
somehow like the drama.

00:35:20.803 --> 00:35:21.970 align:middle line:90%
I'm attracted to that drama.

00:35:21.970 --> 00:35:23.720 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And maybe he doesn't
have to make a commitment.

00:35:23.720 --> 00:35:24.110 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTENSON: Yeah.

00:35:24.110 --> 00:35:25.083 align:middle line:90%
So he's working on it.

00:35:25.083 --> 00:35:26.000 align:middle line:90%
He's getting coaching.

00:35:26.000 --> 00:35:29.030 align:middle line:84%
He's working on it, because
now he's a little older,

00:35:29.030 --> 00:35:33.110 align:middle line:84%
in his 60s, and doesn't want
to just continue on that path.

00:35:33.110 --> 00:35:35.960 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Is it strange
for somebody to not

00:35:35.960 --> 00:35:39.050 align:middle line:84%
want to have a relationship
at all in their life?

00:35:39.050 --> 00:35:39.850 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTENSON: Mm.

00:35:39.850 --> 00:35:42.170 align:middle line:90%
I mean, everybody's different.

00:35:42.170 --> 00:35:43.650 align:middle line:90%
I don't think so.

00:35:43.650 --> 00:35:47.540 align:middle line:84%
But society really
has that message,

00:35:47.540 --> 00:35:49.370 align:middle line:84%
that everybody should
be in love with all

00:35:49.370 --> 00:35:53.075 align:middle line:84%
the messaging and the rom-coms
and the Disney and all that.

00:35:53.075 --> 00:35:54.500 align:middle line:90%
You should have somebody.

00:35:54.500 --> 00:35:57.560 align:middle line:84%
But your path may be
just to be a teacher

00:35:57.560 --> 00:35:59.560 align:middle line:90%
or go within or learn or heal.

00:35:59.560 --> 00:36:01.640 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: I know a guy who
just wants to have fun.

00:36:01.640 --> 00:36:02.960 align:middle line:90%
Just wants to date.

00:36:02.960 --> 00:36:04.530 align:middle line:90%
He just-- he likes his house.

00:36:04.530 --> 00:36:05.480 align:middle line:90%
He likes his cars.

00:36:05.480 --> 00:36:05.990 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTENSON: Right.

00:36:05.990 --> 00:36:07.580 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And he
doesn't want to have

00:36:07.580 --> 00:36:10.590 align:middle line:84%
to worry about a family
or anything like that.

00:36:10.590 --> 00:36:12.260 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTENSON: Nothing
wrong with it.

00:36:12.260 --> 00:36:13.100 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:36:13.100 --> 00:36:14.267 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: You don't think so?

00:36:14.267 --> 00:36:15.680 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTENSON: I don't think so.

00:36:15.680 --> 00:36:19.310 align:middle line:84%
Every individual is--
we're all sovereign beings.

00:36:19.310 --> 00:36:20.300 align:middle line:90%
We can decide.

00:36:20.300 --> 00:36:22.520 align:middle line:84%
Because maybe in some
past lives, I really--

00:36:22.520 --> 00:36:23.900 align:middle line:90%
I like the past life stuff too.

00:36:23.900 --> 00:36:26.810 align:middle line:84%
Maybe he had
relationships that--

00:36:26.810 --> 00:36:28.580 align:middle line:84%
somebody told me--
I was wondering

00:36:28.580 --> 00:36:31.490 align:middle line:84%
why I never had the urge to
have children in this lifetime.

00:36:31.490 --> 00:36:32.960 align:middle line:90%
It never crossed my mind.

00:36:32.960 --> 00:36:36.440 align:middle line:84%
And the spirit guide, he
says, because you've done it.

00:36:36.440 --> 00:36:38.273 align:middle line:84%
You've done it so many
times in past lives.

00:36:38.273 --> 00:36:40.190 align:middle line:84%
You had a lot of kids,
a lot of family around.

00:36:40.190 --> 00:36:42.713 align:middle line:84%
This life was just about
you being with your husband

00:36:42.713 --> 00:36:43.880 align:middle line:90%
and doing some other things.

00:36:43.880 --> 00:36:47.120 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Marla, what causes
a relationship to fizzle out?

00:36:47.120 --> 00:36:48.470 align:middle line:90%
It starts great.

00:36:48.470 --> 00:36:50.300 align:middle line:90%
Sparks fly.

00:36:50.300 --> 00:36:53.940 align:middle line:84%
And then a month, two months,
a year, it ain't the same.

00:36:53.940 --> 00:36:54.740 align:middle line:90%
How come?

00:36:54.740 --> 00:36:56.198 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTENSON: Because
that initial--

00:36:56.198 --> 00:36:58.615 align:middle line:84%
there's nothing more magical
than that initial spark

00:36:58.615 --> 00:36:59.990 align:middle line:84%
when you meet
somebody and you've

00:36:59.990 --> 00:37:03.530 align:middle line:84%
got those hormones flying
and that initial attraction,

00:37:03.530 --> 00:37:04.710 align:middle line:90%
and it's so exciting.

00:37:04.710 --> 00:37:07.880 align:middle line:84%
But then in reality, that's
not going to sustain.

00:37:07.880 --> 00:37:09.860 align:middle line:84%
And some people
have that addiction,

00:37:09.860 --> 00:37:12.740 align:middle line:84%
kind of that high
off of that newness

00:37:12.740 --> 00:37:14.903 align:middle line:84%
that really will not
continue, so you're going

00:37:14.903 --> 00:37:16.070 align:middle line:90%
to move into something else.

00:37:16.070 --> 00:37:20.300 align:middle line:84%
You're going to move into a
deeper relationship or more

00:37:20.300 --> 00:37:21.590 align:middle line:90%
friendship.

00:37:21.590 --> 00:37:23.690 align:middle line:90%
So people want that newness.

00:37:23.690 --> 00:37:26.105 align:middle line:84%
And that's why people
have affairs or break up

00:37:26.105 --> 00:37:27.322 align:middle line:90%
and go for that again.

00:37:27.322 --> 00:37:29.030 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Would you
say that you're almost

00:37:29.030 --> 00:37:30.230 align:middle line:90%
like a psychologist?

00:37:30.230 --> 00:37:33.920 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTENSON: [LAUGHS] Sometimes
I feel like it, you know?

00:37:33.920 --> 00:37:34.920 align:middle line:90%
People need advice.

00:37:34.920 --> 00:37:35.720 align:middle line:90%
They need help.

00:37:35.720 --> 00:37:36.520 align:middle line:90%
They want to talk.

00:37:36.520 --> 00:37:39.440 align:middle line:84%
And that's why I'm now
moving into coaching as well.

00:37:39.440 --> 00:37:41.210 align:middle line:90%
I'm specializing in boundaries.

00:37:41.210 --> 00:37:43.000 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: What kind of coaching?

00:37:43.000 --> 00:37:45.125 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTENSON: Nancy Levin,
who's a Hay House author,

00:37:45.125 --> 00:37:47.000 align:middle line:90%
has a coaching program.

00:37:47.000 --> 00:37:49.100 align:middle line:84%
And it's specializing
in boundaries,

00:37:49.100 --> 00:37:52.830 align:middle line:84%
and I just did a whole year of
study and just got certified.

00:37:52.830 --> 00:37:55.160 align:middle line:84%
So if anybody needs
help with boundaries,

00:37:55.160 --> 00:37:58.410 align:middle line:84%
with co-dependency, if
you're a people pleaser,

00:37:58.410 --> 00:38:01.110 align:middle line:84%
can't say no, always attracting
the wrong kind of person,

00:38:01.110 --> 00:38:02.630 align:middle line:90%
so I can help with that now.

00:38:02.630 --> 00:38:03.430 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Yeah.

00:38:03.430 --> 00:38:07.940 align:middle line:84%
Some people-- I've known
these people through my life,

00:38:07.940 --> 00:38:12.040 align:middle line:84%
like a woman may be attracted
to a guy who can't get a job

00:38:12.040 --> 00:38:13.460 align:middle line:90%
or stays unemployed.

00:38:13.460 --> 00:38:14.520 align:middle line:90%
How does that happen.

00:38:14.520 --> 00:38:15.320 align:middle line:90%
>>MARTENSON: Right.

00:38:15.320 --> 00:38:16.120 align:middle line:90%
Right.

00:38:16.120 --> 00:38:18.320 align:middle line:84%
Well, Nancy, my teacher,
she had the same--

00:38:18.320 --> 00:38:19.830 align:middle line:90%
she had a story about herself.

00:38:19.830 --> 00:38:21.620 align:middle line:84%
She was an overachiever,
and she felt

00:38:21.620 --> 00:38:24.740 align:middle line:84%
her worth was being
a money maker,

00:38:24.740 --> 00:38:27.590 align:middle line:84%
being somebody who made a
lot of money and worked hard.

00:38:27.590 --> 00:38:31.130 align:middle line:84%
And so she'd attract guys
who weren't really working.

00:38:31.130 --> 00:38:32.780 align:middle line:84%
That was like she's
showing her worth.

00:38:32.780 --> 00:38:34.040 align:middle line:84%
Like, I'm going to take
care of everything.

00:38:34.040 --> 00:38:35.540 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to take
care of everybody.

00:38:35.540 --> 00:38:38.480 align:middle line:84%
And so it's a program that's
running from your childhood

00:38:38.480 --> 00:38:41.000 align:middle line:84%
where maybe you thought,
in order to be important

00:38:41.000 --> 00:38:44.443 align:middle line:84%
or to be loved, I have
to take care of everybody

00:38:44.443 --> 00:38:46.110 align:middle line:84%
or I have to do
everything for everyone,

00:38:46.110 --> 00:38:47.540 align:middle line:84%
or I have to make
a lot of money.

00:38:47.540 --> 00:38:48.880 align:middle line:90%
Whatever it is.

00:38:48.880 --> 00:38:50.510 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: It's amazing.

00:38:50.510 --> 00:38:52.310 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTENSON: The
patterns play out.

00:38:52.310 --> 00:38:56.450 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: How important is
people's health, well-being,

00:38:56.450 --> 00:39:00.500 align:middle line:84%
taking care of themselves to
develop that relationship?

00:39:00.500 --> 00:39:02.645 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTENSON: It's
important to people.

00:39:02.645 --> 00:39:03.860 align:middle line:90%
They always ask me, I want--

00:39:03.860 --> 00:39:05.780 align:middle line:84%
I don't want to have to take
care-- especially in the older

00:39:05.780 --> 00:39:07.350 align:middle line:84%
group that I work
in they said, well,

00:39:07.350 --> 00:39:08.840 align:middle line:84%
I don't want to have to
take care of somebody.

00:39:08.840 --> 00:39:10.132 align:middle line:90%
I don't want to be a nursemaid.

00:39:10.132 --> 00:39:12.170 align:middle line:84%
So I don't mind
dating an older guy

00:39:12.170 --> 00:39:16.147 align:middle line:84%
if he's taking care of himself,
if he's fit, if he's active,

00:39:16.147 --> 00:39:16.980 align:middle line:90%
so that's important.

00:39:16.980 --> 00:39:19.605 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What's one of the
next projects for Marla?

00:39:19.605 --> 00:39:21.980 align:middle line:84%
>>MARTENSON: Well, stepping
